<TEXT>
a government review panel has cleared a 
married couple at the department of health and human services of 
violating federal travel rules or taking unauthorized trips at 
government expense according to a published report wednesday 
the departments ethics review board found that the trips by 
terry and paget hinch had been authorized and did involve 
government business the washington post reported 
the panel said in a written report that mrs hinch apparently 
had arranged three legitimate business trips so that she could be 
near her husband at the resort area of orlando fla and over 
thanksgiving near his familys home in the san franciso area 
the board said arranging the trips for the personal 
convenience of the hinches raised an appearance of 
impropriety and noted that it had sought and received voluntary 
reimbursement of 3264 for some costs related to the trips 
however the report added the board does not believe that any 
disciplinary action is warranted by the evidence relating to the 
official travel by terry and paget hinch 
</TEXT>
