<TEXT>
from 1975 to this march 226091 
vietnamese boat people have landed in malaysia an official said 
today 
the influx of vietnamese refugees began in 1975 after us 
forces withdrew from south vietnam and it fell to communist forces 
from north vietnam 
of the 226091 refugees 217812 resettled in other countries 
including 128000 in the united states said eric e morris the 
united nations high commissioner for refugees for malaysia and 
brunei 
in the first three months of this year 2921 boat people 
reached malaysian shores higher than the 1702 for the same period 
last year he said 
morris told reporters the increase was due in part to 
thailands decision to forbid boats of refugees to land on its 
shores 
the boat people generally land on the east coasts of malaysia 
and thailand by cutting across the south china sea 
