<DOCNO> AP880426-0008 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the police chief is vowing to close 
down manilas honkytonk district which he claims had made it the 
sin capital of asia 
his targets are nightspots in the neighborhood known as the 
citys tourist belt where scantily clad girls bump and grind 
to disco music and for a price go out with male customers 
although the ermita district pumps millions of dollars each year 
into the citys economy authorities have called for replacing the 
nightspots with more wholesome family entertainment 
now we are known internationally as the center of the flesh 
trade the sin city of asia brig gen alfredo lim the 
capitals police chief said recently when we hear of this 
reference all of us feel a furious sense of outrage for we all 
know that we dont deserve such notoriety 
however bar owners say the crackdown will cause worse problems 
add to economic hardship and advance the spread of sexual disease 
last month police began raiding bars and discos in the citys 
ermita district they have rounded up more than 2000 barmaids 
known as hospitality girls and detained dozens of foreigners 
who operate some of more than 505 bars restaurants discos 
nightclubs and brothels in ermitas 10block strip 
president corazon aquino has backed the raids saying what we 
should guard against is sacrificing the dignity and honor of the 
filipino woman 
but in a country with many economic problems sex is big 
business 
lim said he expects bar owners mostly americans australians 
west germans japanese and filipinos to fight back by waging a 
smear campaign against him and his police force 
they are employing all tricks to stop us so they can earn 
bundles and bundles of money lim said they are capitalizing 
on our women 
indeed an typical ermita bar earns about 715 dollars on a 
regular day the bigger establishments average about 1666 daily 
but gilbert compuesto general manager of the hollywood show 
palace said the raids have been hurting the oncethriving 
entertainment industry cutting daily earnings by as much as 70 
percent 
moreover ronnie rueda operations manager of a leading club 
called firehouse said closing bars will force tens of thousands of 
manila prostitutes to go underground she says that will make it 
difficult to trace carriers of acquired immune deficiency syndrome 
and venereal diseases 
lim said 80 percent of 2000 women picked up in the raids have 
been found suffering from venereal disease the department of 
health said at least 50 filipinos mostly hospitality girls have 
been infected with the aids virus but none has developed its 
active symptoms 
the problem of venereal disease will spread out because the 
women will become freelancers they will hang around hotels and 
restaurants rueda said who will manage them and check them 
for diseases 
compuesto said his group has offered to help police by closing 
some establishments and ridding the area of freelance prostitutes 
but he says their offer has been ignored 
if they are really trying to cure the problem of morality 
this campaign should be nationwide compuesto said how can 
they solve immorality prostitution or drug abuse if they are only 
concentrating on ermita 
other critics say closing ermitas seedy establishments would 
force some displaced workers into a life of crime if youre 
starving and youre the only breadwinner in the family i think 
there is nothing else to do said kit samson a disc jockey 
compuesto said most bar girls are earning more than the 3 
minimum daily wage of factory workers not counting what they earn 
once they leave the bars with customers 
thousands of people dont have jobs we have jobs that we 
enjoy but now they want to get it from us compuesto said 
what kind of logic is that 
its really a hypocrisy of people to say that when tourists 
come to the philippines they just want to see the sights in 
tagaytay baguio or some other part of the country compuesto 
said they need entertainment 
</TEXT>
