nunn has said that no matter what inducements might be offered 
his interest in the vice presidency is just about one on a scale of 
10 
but he has never said never 
no vice president has ever served simultaneously as secretary of 
defense 
no vice president has ever served simultaneously as a member of 
a presidents cabinet 
but a number of people who became vice president had previously 
served in presidential cabinets 
john c calhoun served as vice president in one period and as 
secretary of state at another 
presidents have appointed vice presidents to task forces on one 
subject or another 
president reagan named vice president george bush to head a task 
force on drugs and narcotics president john f kennedy named his 
vice president lyndon b johnson to head a task force on space 
exploration 
other vice presidents have had a strong influence on their 
administrations but that has been the rare exception rather than 
the rule 
while not barred by the constitution a vice president 
simultaneously serving as secretary of defense might well discover 
a thicket of unexpected conflicts 
while the vice president has his job by election a cabinet 
officer must be confirmed by the senate 
the only job specifically assigned the vice president by the 
constitution is to serve as president of the senate 
unexpected strains might arise if the senate were asked to 
confirm its own presiding office to serve as well in a cabinet post 
in the role of the senates presiding officer the vice 
presidents only real power is his ability to cast tiebreaking 
votes at moments of legislative impasse 
some senators might demand that a vice president who was also 
the secretary of defense abstain from breaking a tie on closely 
divided defense issues directly affecting his department 
such a decision would deprive the administration of its ability 
to decide the issue in its favor by breaking the tie 
since 1981 bush has broken seven ties five of them on defense 
issues 
secretaries of defense routinely testify before congressional 
committees in defense of military budgets there is some potential 
awkwardness in a situation when the witness is also president of 
the senate 
concern might also be triggered if it became necessary for an 
elected vice president also serving as secretary of defense to 
travel with a president to an overseas conference 
that would place both the president and vice president out of 
the country at the same time and that might become a more 
worrisome situation if the country they were visiting were the 
soviet union 
naming nunn the national security adviser might create fewer 
such problems since the person who fills that post is not confirmed 
by the senate 
the vice presidency has not always been a happy post for the 
person who held the job many have complained it consists of little 
more than attending the funerals of foreign leaders 
john adams the nations first vice president had some thoughts 
on his job which he shared with his colleagues on the eve of a 
visit to their chamber by president washington 
gentlemen i feel great difficulty in how to act adams 
said 
i am possessed of two separate powers i am vice president in 
this i am nothing but i may be everything 
but i am president also of the senate when the president 
comes into the senate what shall i be 
some politicians are still thinking about what a vice president 
shall be at least when sam nunns name comes up for discussion 
