five southwest kansas counties beat a federal deadline for 
conservation planning says the agriculture department 
wilson scaling chief of the departments soil conservation 
service said monday a consulting company john ho and associates 
inc dallas texas completed planning by midapril less than 
half the time called for in its oneyear contract 
the 1985 farm law gives farmers until dec 31 1989 to complete 
conservation plans for protecting highly erodible land scaling 
said district conservationists in kansas said they would not be 
able to help all the farmers with planning in time to meet the 
deadline 
one of the most successful ideas was to contract out the 
planning to a qualified private company he said 
kansas has the secondlargest amount of cropland of any state 
