the associated press will speed its datastream 
news delivery service to about 9000 words a minute and increase 
its domestic news staff to deal with what its president calls the 
the new world of news 
the increase to 9000 words a minute begins in june and the ap 
also will offer new photo and graphic services ap president louis 
d boccardi told publishers and newspaper editors monday at the 
annual ap meeting 
the news cooperative also will add 10 to 15 domestic news 
staffers in 1988 to better serve the aps 1423 newspaper members 
he said 
the bulk of these will go to our line bureaus whose state and 
regional news coverage is so important to you he told the 
members with membership increasing as it has the demands on our 
state bureaus are increasing and we must meet those needs 
the worldwide news cooperative is about to move from a speed of 
about 1050 words a minute to about 9000 on its datastream and 
datafeature wires datastream is the ap highspeed news wire 
datafeature is a separate service that delivers supplemental and 
syndicate copy to member newspapers throughout the system 
for newspapers with systems that need slower speeds the 
delivery can be reduced but the higher capacity will avoid 
crowding that can slow the delivery of copy much like traffic 
clogs a highway 
we are raising the speed limit from 55 miles per hour to 440 
miles per hour and if that werent enough were widening the ap 
interstate from four lanes to eight boccardi said 
a new ap electronic darkroom for large newspapers already is 
serving three members in june the ap will unveil a pcbased 
electronic darkroom designed for smaller newspapers boccardi said 
