<TEXT>
political leaders are telling danes 
to choose in upcoming elections between nato allies and the 
countrys longstanding ban on nuclear weapons 
prime minister poul schlueter a nato backer called the 
parliamentary elections for may 10 urging voters to take a 
stand in favor of the western military alliance 
the sudden storm over denmarks role in the 16nation alliance 
came as a surprise to many voters the peacetime ban on nuclear 
weapons has been in effect for three decades and a shaky coalition 
government has been struggling with economic not military issues 
indeed some voters say economic troubles remain the chief issue 
its not just a question about nuclear weapons but about the 
way the government runs society said susane nielsen a 
conservative voter who works in a health insurance office we 
have to face these economic problems 
the unexpected showdown began april 14 when the leftist 
opposition pushed through a parliamentary resolution intended to 
strengthen the countrys ban on peacetime nuclear weapons 
the move which has been delayed pending the election requires 
the government to notify individual warships of the countrys ban 
parliamentary negotiators have not decided if the ships would then 
have to respond 
until now denmark has simply stated its policy to one and all 
some allies reacted sharply to the latest proposal warning it 
jeopardizes denmarks participation in nato a meeting of natos 
nuclear planning group was rescheduled from denmark to belgium 
britain called off naval maneuvers in denmark 
