said one is to dig a parallel well and draw off the oil and gas 
feeding the fire the other is the americans way with an 
explosion that uses up oxygen and kills the fire 
petrobras plans to import an additional 60000 barrels of oil a 
day at a cost of about 1 million to cover most of the loss of 
production from enchova 
the platform itself cost 330 million and is covered by 
insurance a few towers fell down but apparently it will not be 
destroyed by the fire pinto said 
the campos basin is brazils richest oil region and has produced 
370000 barrels daily but brazil still needs more oil and imports 
in the first quarter averaged 718000 barrels per day 
