following is a translation by the 
associated press of the saudi arabian governments memorandum on 
the rupture of ties with iran 
in view of the iranian hostile attitude toward the kingdom of 
saudi arabia the premeditated offenses to basic saudi interests 
and as a result of the iranian government attitude that runs 
counter to the principles of international law and diplomatic 
traditions 
on account of irans violation of the principles of good 
neighborliness and mutual respect as exemplified in the attempt to 
smuggle explosives into the kingdom during the pilgrimage season of 
the year 1406 1986 to imperil the safety of pilgrims and the 
sacred places 
because of irans manipulation of religious rituals and its 
instigation of dissent and unrest among the sons of the islamic 
nation 
due to irans repeated attempts to harm the basic interests of 
the kingdom and its obstruction of free navigation by raiding 
ships sailing to and from saudi arabia in addition to other forms 
of terrorism and subversion 
the kingdom has resorted to the attitude of selfrestraint and 
prudence required between two neighboring islamic countries it 
tried through various channels to explain to iran that the kingdom 
was eager to normalize relations on the basis of mutual respect 
but the kingdoms positive stance gained no response whatever 
from the iranian side which persisted in perpetrating hostile 
practices 
foremost among these practices was the ransacking of the tehran 
embassy of king fahd the custodian of the two holy shrines one 
saudi diplomat was killed embassy documents were looted and its 
property destroyed in that attack in addition the iranian 
authorities had failed to provide adequate security for the embassy 
personnel who were perpetually harassed forcing them all to leave 
tehran 
therefore the government of saudi arabia decided to break its 
ties with the islamic republic of iran and asked all personnel of 
the iranian embassy in riyadh and consulate general in jiddah to 
leave the kingdom within a week 
