officials of various un agencies will meet in new york 
thursday to distribute tasks in the repatriation said unhcr 
sources who spoke on the condition of anonymity un 
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar is expected to appoint a 
special program coordinator shortly as was done during the african 
drought emergency 
perez de cuellar told a news conference tuesday that un 
observers will soon be deployed to monitor withdrawal of soviet 
troops from afghanistan and a political settlement he said the 
security council authorized him to proceed with the un mission 
our operation will be very much on in the next few days he 
said 
faubert said in an interview with the associated press that 
unhcr intends to supervise protection for the returnees organize 
transportation back to their place of origin and oversee the 
initial distribution of food seeds and agricultural tools after 
they return a communications network to monitor the different 
parts of the program must also be built 
the effort is expected to cost hundreds of millions of dollars 
if all afghans return un refugee commissioner jeanpierre hocke 
has said 
perez de cuellar is expected to launch an appeal for money soon 
our people are drawing up a number of scenarios that go from a 
massive rush to people not moving very quickly in pakistan there 
are about 20 different scenarios faubert said 
he said it is also difficult to predict whether the refugees 
will return to several areas simultaneously or move region by 
region 
apart from logistics un officials are evaluating what aid is 
needed to rebuild roads and dwellings and restore land in 
afghanistan 
more than a third of the population fled during 10 years of 
civil war official figures list 31 million afghan refugees in 
pakistan and 24 million in iran 
under a unsponsored agreement signed april 14 the soviet 
union pledged to withdraw its troops backing the afghan government 
starting may 15 afghanistan and pakistan agreed to ensure the safe 
and voluntary return of refugees 
not signing were moslem afghan guerrillas who say they will 
continue fighting to overthrow the communist kabul government 
unhcr officials in pakistan met with the resistance shortly 
before the pacts conclusion apparently aiming to draw them into 
the repatriation plans faubert refused to reveal the outcome of 
the talks but said they will continue 
un plans must also take into account the differences between 
government policy and the composition of the refugee population in 
iran and pakistan 
most afghans in pakistan are displaced farmers housed in 320 
refugee villages within about 60 miles of the border they own 
about 4000 private trucks so there could be sizeable 
unsupervised returns 
in iran about 60 percent of the afghan refugees are in cities 
relatively far from the border many are said to have found menial 
jobs they may wait for years to return faubert said 
iran which did not take part in the un negotiations and 
pakistan both pledge not to expel refugees but pakistani officials 
make clear they would welcome a quick return home of the afghans 
many pakistanis blame the refugees for a wide range of the 
countrys social and economic problems 
