<TEXT>
ah belo corp said monday its earnings declined 
by 59 percent in the first quarter of 1988 from the same period 
last year due to higher operating costs and weak advertising 
demand 
the media company posted a profit of 896000 or 9 cents per 
share on revenue of 873 million during the three months ended 
march 31 that compared with earnings of 22 million or 20 cents 
per share on revenue of 875 million in first quarter 1987 
excluding revenue from two denver radio stations sold in 1987 
first quarter revenue would have been up by 19 million from a 
year earlier belo stated 
the company attributed the profit decline to higher broadcast 
programming costs higher newsprint costs and weak advertising 
demand 
belo owns the dallas morning news and dallasfort worth suburban 
newspapers inc publisher of seven community newspapers it also 
owns and operates five networkaffiliated television stations 
the dallas morning news publishing revenue dipped to 507 
million from 509 million a year earlier due to a sharply lower 
volume of advertising belo stated 
broadcasting revenue rose only slightly during the quarter but 
