<TEXT>
an opec oil minister reacting to us 
criticism of the cartels talks with nonopec nations said tuesday 
that closer ties among oil producers was in the interest of all 
countries 
opec is not against anybody said arturo hernandez grisanti 
the oil minister of venezuela 
opec is making efforts to stabilize the oil market and this 
stability is in the interests of everybody including consumers 
he said adding that this was true even in the case of the united 
states 
hernandez made the unprompted remarks as he entered an evening 
meeting of oil officials from six organization of petroleum 
exporting countries and representatives of seven nonopec oil 
exporters including mexico china and egypt 
the two groups were exploring means of cooperation including 
possible joint cuts or restraints on oil production their aim is 
to push prices up to opecs target of 18 a barrel 
us energy secretary john herrington speaking during a recent 
tour of independent oilproducing nations criticized opec for 
seeking to collaborate with other countries he said the vienna 
talks were doomed to failure 
i cant really understand why secretary herrington made such 
aggressive attacks against opec hernandez said 
the minister said opecs sole intention was to reach a 
rational level in the price of oil 
i dont believe this is against the national interests of the 
united states he said the united states is the country with 
the highest cost of oil production 
he noted that proven oil reserves and production levels in the 
united states have fallen sharply since world oil prices collapsed 
two years ago 
the united states was not invited to the vienna meeting kent 
hance a member of the texas railroad commission which regulates 
that states oil industry was here however to meet individually 
with opec and nonopec oil officials 
